(2024 Beginning of Autumn, Beijing)

4
00:01:57,590 --> 00:01:59,150
Tong Leyi, a great discovery!

5
00:01:59,150 --> 00:02:00,150
A great discovery!

6
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,300
I've sent it to your WeChat.

7
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:04,740
I found a picture
on Dai Daji's birthday post

8
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:06,430
on Weibo.

9
00:02:06,430 --> 00:02:07,950
Are there two people

10
00:02:07,950 --> 00:02:09,630
in the reflection on the wine glass

11
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:11,030
beside the sashimi platter?

12
00:02:11,310 --> 00:02:12,510
The one on the left is Ms. Dai.

13
00:02:12,790 --> 00:02:14,070
The man on the right...

14
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:15,630
Why are they so close together?

15
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,700
Who is this?

16
00:02:16,790 --> 00:02:17,820
Let me zoom in.

17
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:19,470
It's blurry.

18
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:21,140
Let me enhance the picture.

19
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:23,140
Got it.

20
00:02:24,260 --> 00:02:25,310
Who is this?

21
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,580
It's not Zhou Shui.

22
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:31,070
Who is he?

23
00:02:34,140 --> 00:02:37,510
I think I saw someone
wearing this cap in the office.

24
00:02:38,310 --> 00:02:39,790
Gosh! It's Lin Chenxing!

25
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:41,380
Lin Chenxing?

26
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:43,030
Who is Lin Chenxing?

27
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:44,580
Don't you know Lin Chenxing?

28
00:02:44,980 --> 00:02:46,630
He has many fans on Weibo

29
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,070
and is very popular now.

30
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:50,750
He is the male lead of Ms. Dai's film.

31
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:51,920
(Lin Chenxing)
Look at his cap.

32
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:54,320
It's the same as the one
on the reflection of the wine glass.

33
00:02:56,420 --> 00:02:57,660
Why is it him?

34
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,380
Look. This is Lin Chenxing, right?

35
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:02,980
The one beside him is Ms. Dai.

36
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:04,260
This is so exciting.

37
00:03:04,260 --> 00:03:06,070
I wonder what Ms. Dai would say.

38
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:07,660
Leyi.

39
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:08,760
Come and see this.

40
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:09,880
- What is it?
- Look at this.

41
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,420
There's even a video.

42
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:13,140
It's trending immediately. Look.

43
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:13,910
What is trending?

44
00:03:13,910 --> 00:03:15,820
Yesterday,
Lin Chenxing went home with Daji...

45
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:16,040
What?

46
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:17,600
Their pictures were taken by paparazzi.

47
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,040
Let me see.

48
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,230
I wonder if it's true.

49
00:03:20,350 --> 00:03:22,380
Oh no. This proves it.

50
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:24,070
Mr. Hong is here.

51
00:03:24,230 --> 00:03:24,540
Hurry.

52
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,310
He has come here?

53
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:25,980
Let's go.

54
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:26,580
What?

55
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,540
(Boycott Huanteng Films)

56
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:35,310
Hello, Mr. Hong.

57
00:03:35,380 --> 00:03:36,310
Where is Dai Daji?

58
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:38,140
Who is this?

59
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:41,580
The terrifying Mr. Hong.

60
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:42,760
This is a serious matter now.

61
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:44,660
Get her out here.

62
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:46,840
(The Four, Filming Ceremony)
Geng!

63
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:49,660
(2011 Beginning of Autumn, Beijing)
All right. I'm going to be there soon.

64
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:50,260
Geng!

65
00:03:50,260 --> 00:03:51,070
Everyone,

66
00:03:51,140 --> 00:03:53,190
please cooperate and not stand here.

67
00:03:53,190 --> 00:03:54,750
We are filming inside.

68
00:03:54,790 --> 00:03:56,070
Please help us out, all right?

69
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:58,350
Is Geng coming today, Security?

70
00:03:58,660 --> 00:03:59,750
I'm not a security guard.

71
00:04:01,660 --> 00:04:02,230
Daji.

72
00:04:02,230 --> 00:04:02,750
Hurry.

73
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:03,470
What's going on?

74
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,510
Why did they ask you
to carry the lunch boxes?

75
00:04:07,230 --> 00:04:09,260
There's no choice. We are "orphans".

76
00:04:09,950 --> 00:04:10,980
We have the lowest status.

77
00:04:11,380 --> 00:04:12,350
Time to eat!

78
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:15,860
Time to eat!

79
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:18,070
Actor's assistant!

80
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:19,870
Geng's lunchbox today.

81
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:20,780
He's not eating today.

82
00:04:20,780 --> 00:04:21,580
He's not eating?

83
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:22,580
That's wonderful.

84
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:26,190
Why are you so excited
about distributing lunch boxes?

85
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:27,020
I feel happy.

86
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:28,990
Here you go.

87
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,240
Do you think we've come
to Shendu Pictures

88
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:32,430
just to distribute lunchboxes?

89
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:35,280
I'm not going to accept this.

90
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:37,800
We should work together
and create a miracle

91
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,260
instead of distributing lunch boxes.

92
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:40,260
Me too.

93
00:04:40,430 --> 00:04:41,460
So, I've decided

94
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:44,190
to give myself a drumstick today.

95
00:04:45,380 --> 00:04:46,900
Daji, you're amazing.

96
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:48,380
Where's my lunchbox?

97
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:51,700
Preserved Vegetable Pork Belly.

98
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:52,870
Kung Pao Chicken.

99
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:53,950
Sweet and Sour Tenderloin.

100
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:56,140
Fried Mushrooms.
Stir-fried Shredded Potato.

101
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:57,310
It's a feast.

102
00:04:57,780 --> 00:05:00,260
Aren't they going to eat
all these dishes?

103
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,140
We got lucky.

104
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:09,670
Let's eat.

105
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:10,670
Let's eat.

106
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:12,780
Don't eat rice first.

107
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:13,990
Eat the meat.

108
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:14,900
Eat the meat.

109
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:16,220
Gosh.

110
00:05:16,780 --> 00:05:18,260
Look at this fatty tenderloin.

111
00:05:21,670 --> 00:05:22,430
It's so satisfying.

112
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:25,870
Tell me.

113
00:05:27,310 --> 00:05:29,630
Are we going
to distribute lunchboxes our whole life?

114
00:05:29,780 --> 00:05:30,460
No way.

115
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:35,340
Our crew has been disbanded
and we aren't allowed to shoot films.

116
00:05:35,990 --> 00:05:37,580
What's the meaning of staying here?

117
00:05:38,110 --> 00:05:39,020
What do you mean?

118
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:40,220
Are you quitting?

119
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:41,340
I was wondering

120
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:44,430
if I should resign.

121
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:46,430
Resigning is easy.

122
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:48,630
When can we get another job?

123
00:05:48,752 --> 00:05:49,580
Let's find one.

124
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:51,310
We'll surely get a job.

125
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:54,460
However,

126
00:05:54,460 --> 00:05:57,000
what will you do during this period
when you're looking for a job?

127
00:05:57,430 --> 00:05:58,550
How can you pay for rent?

128
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:00,240
How can you pay for the utility bill?

129
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,720
How can you pay for social insurance?

130
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,220
We are still staying in Yanjiao.

131
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,510
It rhymes.

132
00:06:08,460 --> 00:06:09,340
You are gifted.

133
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:12,070
So,

134
00:06:12,190 --> 00:06:13,670
who will pay these expenses for us?

135
00:06:13,670 --> 00:06:14,380
I don't want

136
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:15,820
to return to our past lives.

137
00:06:19,190 --> 00:06:20,460
We can't resign indeed.

138
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,700
I dare not.

139
00:06:22,430 --> 00:06:24,380
I will never dare to resign again.

140
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:29,990
Zhou Shui! Daji!

141
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:36,110
I was wondering where both of you were.
Having a feast here?

142
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:39,310
Come and find me later.
I have something to tell you later.

143
00:06:40,877 --> 00:06:42,670
There's no need to hide it.
I saw everything.

144
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,674
Take your time.
Come and find me after you're done!

145
00:06:48,580 --> 00:06:50,460
What's the crime of
stealing lunchboxes?

146
00:06:51,820 --> 00:06:53,020
I think it'll be fine.

147
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:54,510
I think so too.

148
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,700
I want to ask you about something.

149
00:06:58,550 --> 00:07:00,220
Tell me about your future plans

150
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:01,990
and what you want to do.

151
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,220
We will obey any arrangements
and work seriously.

152
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:06,220
Tell me the truth.

153
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:09,950
I want to shoot a film.

154
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,190
I'm leaving Shendu Pictures

155
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,750
and establishing my own company.

156
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:17,340
The only people I want with me

157
00:07:18,190 --> 00:07:19,110
are both of you.

158
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:23,140
Don't you have any questions for me?

159
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:24,510
Why us?

160
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,320
Both of you are young

161
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:27,700
and have ideas.

162
00:07:28,140 --> 00:07:29,260
You only lack opportunities.

163
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:32,240
Shendu Pictures
can't give you opportunities

164
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:33,750
but I can.

165
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,140
Is the opportunity you speak of

166
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,510
an opportunity to shoot a film?

167
00:07:38,820 --> 00:07:40,430
The company has just been founded.

168
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:42,380
We still need to make the videos

169
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:44,340
we used to film.

170
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,070
Don't overthink.

171
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:48,780
Every famous director in the world

172
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:51,550
begins by filming low-budget movies.

173
00:07:51,990 --> 00:07:53,950
Nolan. Spielberg.

174
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:54,950
Zhang Yimou. Chen Kaige.

175
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:56,260
All of them are the same.

176
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,700
I trust your abilities.

177
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:59,800
Both of you won't be making
low-budget films forever.

178
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:00,510
Right?

179
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:01,460
Yes.

180
00:08:01,780 --> 00:08:02,430
Yes.

181
00:08:03,140 --> 00:08:03,870
However...

182
00:08:04,070 --> 00:08:04,550
Well...

183
00:08:04,950 --> 00:08:07,780
The weather doesn't suit
such inspirational words.

184
00:08:07,950 --> 00:08:09,260
It doesn't feel right.

185
00:08:09,670 --> 00:08:11,020
The harder it is in life,

186
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:12,670
the more you need to build hope.

187
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:14,780
If there's no problem,

188
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:17,550
go and get your resignation processed
with the HR department.

189
00:08:18,950 --> 00:08:19,580
That's right.

190
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:23,110
Don't let anyone know about this.

191
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:25,440
Do you have any more questions?

192
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,400
If we resign now,

193
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,000
what will happen
to our salary this month

194
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,550
and social insurance?

195
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,190
Get your resignation processed first.

196
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,270
Both of your files

197
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:37,910
will be transferred
to my company directly.

198
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:39,640
Your social insurance
will not be terminated.

199
00:08:39,670 --> 00:08:40,500
As for your salary,

200
00:08:41,310 --> 00:08:42,740
I'll pay you 1,000 yuan more

201
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:43,950
from what you are earning

202
00:08:43,980 --> 00:08:45,220
at this place.

203
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,480
Bonus and commission
are extra, what do you think?

204
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,100
Sure.

205
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,270
That's wonderful.

206
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:51,820
Do you feel relieved now?

207
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:53,860
Thanks, Zhaoyang.

208
00:08:54,860 --> 00:08:55,700
Zhaoyang.

209
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:57,480
I have one last question.

210
00:09:03,580 --> 00:09:05,460
Can we really make a film in the end?

211
00:09:07,220 --> 00:09:08,030
Don't worry.

212
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:08,820
If you work with me,

213
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,100
I will be responsible

214
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,500
for your future.

215
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:14,550
Believe in me and believe in yourselves.

216
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,670
We will surely make a film.

217
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:48,440
Are you feeling reluctant to leave?

218
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:52,550
I think I should stand here for a while

219
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:54,980
at this time and place.

220
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:59,220
Just a while?

221
00:10:00,310 --> 00:10:02,390
Just a while.

222
00:10:04,430 --> 00:10:05,220
Tell me.

223
00:10:06,430 --> 00:10:09,950
Will our time at Shendu Pictures
be the highlight of our lives?

224
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:10,740
No.

225
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,880
It'll be after leaving this place.

226
00:10:18,883 --> 00:10:23,460
(2011 Winter, Beijing)

227
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:25,820
Shui!

228
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:33,740
The scene is almost ready.

229
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:34,550
Go and take a look.

230
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,740
Wait. I'm a little nervous.

231
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:38,070
You put a train in your script

232
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:40,310
but I didn't expect Zhaoyang
to get us a real train.

233
00:10:40,550 --> 00:10:42,310
Isn't it a good thing?
Why do you feel nervous?

234
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:45,310
It's because
we were poor at Shendu Pictures.

235
00:10:45,620 --> 00:10:46,200
I don't know

236
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,120
how to film a scene
that costs more than 100 yuan.

237
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:50,620
You are so low-class.

238
00:10:51,430 --> 00:10:52,550
You are a director.

239
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,400
We will be shooting a film
with a budget of 20 million yuan next.

240
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:57,430
Stand tall.

241
00:10:57,980 --> 00:10:58,820
Can you do it?

242
00:10:59,790 --> 00:11:00,390
Yes!

243
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:02,580
Let's go!

244
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:04,030
Let's go!

245
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,150
Get to work.

246
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:10,580
The director is here.

247
00:11:10,740 --> 00:11:11,670
Hello, Director!

248
00:11:11,950 --> 00:11:14,820
Hello, Director!

249
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:15,500
Hello!

250
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:16,480
Good morning, Director.

251
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:16,950
Morning.

252
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:17,700
Hello, Director.

253
00:11:17,950 --> 00:11:18,580
Hello.

254
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:19,700
Hello, Director.

255
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:20,340
Hello.

256
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:22,550
Director, your coffee.

257
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:23,580
Thank you.

258
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,430
Everyone, get ready.

259
00:11:25,740 --> 00:11:26,740
Get ready!

260
00:11:31,620 --> 00:11:32,460
Get to work!

261
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:33,740
Get to work!

262
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:34,790
Sure!

263
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:35,740
Move faster!

264
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,430
Stop walking and start running!

265
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:40,030
Quick! Let's get to work!

266
00:11:42,310 --> 00:11:43,100
"Dull Love Story".

267
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:43,950
Scene one. Take one.

268
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:44,580
Action.

269
00:11:45,820 --> 00:11:47,860
Push in.

270
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:49,430
Let's change another scene.

271
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:49,910
Li,

272
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:51,150
get me a close-up.

273
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:52,670
I want a pan like this.

274
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:53,340
I want to see

275
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:54,310
every word clearly.

276
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:56,390
Yes. Give me
a tighter shot of the product.

277
00:11:57,950 --> 00:11:59,070
